"{\"uid\": \"thenation.com-article-world-paris-olympics-homeless-displacement\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"Forgot Your Password?\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 23, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Your Password\", \"from\": 7, \"to\": 20}]}, {\"sentence\": \"New toThe Nation?Subscribe Print subscriber?Activateyour online access Paris will almost certainly be remembered as a successful Olympic site.\", \"from\": 25, \"to\": 169, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 98, \"end\": 103, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.0239926544066172e-28, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"New toThe Nation?Subscribe Print\", \"from\": 25, \"to\": 57}, {\"ngram\": \"subscriber?Activateyour online access\", \"from\": 58, \"to\": 95}, {\"ngram\": \"a successful Olympic site\", \"from\": 141, \"to\": 166}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Such recollections, however, will leave out those who suffered under its weight.\", \"from\": 170, \"to\": 250, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Such recollections\", \"from\": 170, \"to\": 188}, {\"ngram\": \"its weight\", \"from\": 239, \"to\": 249}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A women seated during the installation of an encampment at the Bastille to demand accommodation for homeless people in Paris on August 6, 2024.\", \"from\": 252, \"to\": 395, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 315, \"end\": 323, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bastille\", \"score\": 0.999999641930181, \"rank\": 3.580695461255166e-07, \"text\": \"Bastille\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bastille\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bastille\"}, {\"begin\": 371, \"end\": 376, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.0239926544066172e-28, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A women\", \"from\": 252, \"to\": 259}, {\"ngram\": \"the installation\", \"from\": 274, \"to\": 290}, {\"ngram\": \"an encampment\", \"from\": 294, \"to\": 307}, {\"ngram\": \"accommodation\", \"from\": 334, \"to\": 347}, {\"ngram\": \"homeless people\", \"from\": 352, \"to\": 367}, {\"ngram\": \"August\", \"from\": 380, \"to\": 386}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As the Paris 2024 sporting spectacle crescendos this week, a less conspicuous struggle continues outside the Olympic zone: a war on the poor.\", \"from\": 397, \"to\": 538, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 404, \"end\": 414, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.430791658852857e-24, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a less conspicuous struggle\", \"from\": 456, \"to\": 483}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic zone\", \"from\": 502, \"to\": 518}, {\"ngram\": \"a war\", \"from\": 520, \"to\": 525}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Inside the Olympic bubble, high-stakes medal events are scheduled every day, while outside the five-ring fever dream the stakes are brutal and the contrast is stark.\", \"from\": 539, \"to\": 704, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Olympic bubble\", \"from\": 546, \"to\": 564}, {\"ngram\": \"high-stakes medal events\", \"from\": 566, \"to\": 590}, {\"ngram\": \"the five-ring fever dream\", \"from\": 630, \"to\": 655}, {\"ngram\": \"the stakes\", \"from\": 656, \"to\": 666}, {\"ngram\": \"the contrast\", \"from\": 682, \"to\": 694}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The Olympic city is hell for the poor,\\\" said Paul Alauzy, of M\\u00e9decins du Monde (Doctors of the World).\", \"from\": 705, \"to\": 808, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The Olympic city\", \"from\": 706, \"to\": 722}, {\"ngram\": \"hell\", \"from\": 726, \"to\": 730}, {\"ngram\": \"Paul Alauzy\", \"from\": 751, \"to\": 762}, {\"ngram\": \"M\\u00e9decins du Monde\", \"from\": 767, \"to\": 784}, {\"ngram\": \"(Doctors\", \"from\": 785, \"to\": 793}, {\"ngram\": \"the World\", \"from\": 797, \"to\": 806}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"At the middle of it you have an Eden [the Olympics].\", \"from\": 809, \"to\": 862, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the middle\", \"from\": 813, \"to\": 823}, {\"ngram\": \"an Eden\", \"from\": 839, \"to\": 846}, {\"ngram\": \"[the Olympics\", \"from\": 847, \"to\": 860}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Everyone wants to participate.\", \"from\": 863, \"to\": 893, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Everyone\", \"from\": 863, \"to\": 871}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They are watching it, but they can not get in.\\\"\", \"from\": 894, \"to\": 941, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"What we have witnessed here in Paris is part of a larger, ignominious Olympic tradition: the brass-knuckled displacement of working-class and poor people to clear space for the Games, whether inSeoulin 1988,Atlantain 1996,Beijingin 2008, orRio de Janeiroin 2016.\", \"from\": 943, \"to\": 1205, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 974, \"end\": 979, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.0239926544066172e-28, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"part\", \"from\": 983, \"to\": 987}, {\"ngram\": \"a larger, ignominious Olympic tradition\", \"from\": 991, \"to\": 1030}, {\"ngram\": \"the brass-knuckled displacement\", \"from\": 1032, \"to\": 1063}, {\"ngram\": \"working-class and poor people\", \"from\": 1067, \"to\": 1096}, {\"ngram\": \"clear space\", \"from\": 1100, \"to\": 1111}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 1116, \"to\": 1125}, {\"ngram\": \"whether inSeoulin\", \"from\": 1127, \"to\": 1144}, {\"ngram\": \"orRio\", \"from\": 1181, \"to\": 1186}, {\"ngram\": \"Janeiroin\", \"from\": 1190, \"to\": 1199}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Melora Koepke, a geographer who splits her time between Paris and Vancouver, Canada, and whose research operates at the nexus of displacement, poverty, and drug use, told us that \\\"people who are deemed undesirable in public space\\\" have borne the brunt of state repression and that \\\"this has accelerated because of the Olympics.\\\"\", \"from\": 1207, \"to\": 1535, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1263, \"end\": 1268, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.0239926544066172e-28, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1273, \"end\": 1282, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vancouver\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5743116472111264e-27, \"text\": \"Vancouver\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vancouver\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vancouver\"}, {\"begin\": 1284, \"end\": 1290, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2950836158906192e-27, \"text\": \"Canada\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Melora Koepke\", \"from\": 1207, \"to\": 1220}, {\"ngram\": \"a geographer\", \"from\": 1222, \"to\": 1234}, {\"ngram\": \"her time\", \"from\": 1246, \"to\": 1254}, {\"ngram\": \"whose research\", \"from\": 1296, \"to\": 1310}, {\"ngram\": \"the nexus\", \"from\": 1323, \"to\": 1332}, {\"ngram\": \"displacement, poverty\", \"from\": 1336, \"to\": 1357}, {\"ngram\": \"drug use\", \"from\": 1363, \"to\": 1371}, {\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 1378, \"to\": 1380}, {\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 1387, \"to\": 1393}, {\"ngram\": \"public space\", \"from\": 1424, \"to\": 1436}, {\"ngram\": \"the brunt\", \"from\": 1449, \"to\": 1458}, {\"ngram\": \"state repression\", \"from\": 1462, \"to\": 1478}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 1521, \"to\": 1533}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The contrast between the glitzy Paris Olympics, where a ticket to the closing ceremony at the Stade de France cancost\\u20ac1,600, and those pushed to the margins of French society could not be more stark.\", \"from\": 1537, \"to\": 1736, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1569, \"end\": 1583, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paris Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1631, \"end\": 1646, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Stade de France\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\"}, {\"begin\": 1697, \"end\": 1703, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9735945908924327, \"rank\": 0.02712089698576202, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The contrast\", \"from\": 1537, \"to\": 1549}, {\"ngram\": \"a ticket\", \"from\": 1591, \"to\": 1599}, {\"ngram\": \"the closing ceremony\", \"from\": 1603, \"to\": 1623}, {\"ngram\": \"the margins\", \"from\": 1682, \"to\": 1693}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We got a glimpse of this reality while out on a night of outreach-or amaraude-with a team from M\\u00e9decins du Monde, consisting of a doctor, two translators, and two outreach specialists.\", \"from\": 1737, \"to\": 1921, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a glimpse\", \"from\": 1744, \"to\": 1753}, {\"ngram\": \"this reality\", \"from\": 1757, \"to\": 1769}, {\"ngram\": \"a night\", \"from\": 1783, \"to\": 1790}, {\"ngram\": \"outreach\", \"from\": 1794, \"to\": 1802}, {\"ngram\": \"amaraude\", \"from\": 1806, \"to\": 1814}, {\"ngram\": \"a team\", \"from\": 1820, \"to\": 1826}, {\"ngram\": \"M\\u00e9decins du Monde\", \"from\": 1832, \"to\": 1849}, {\"ngram\": \"a doctor\", \"from\": 1865, \"to\": 1873}, {\"ngram\": \"two translators\", \"from\": 1875, \"to\": 1890}, {\"ngram\": \"two outreach specialists\", \"from\": 1896, \"to\": 1920}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Our first stop was Bobigny in Saint Denis, an area in the north of Paris that Olympic organizersvowedwould benefit from hosting the Games.\", \"from\": 1923, \"to\": 2061, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1942, \"end\": 1949, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bobigny\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.5392865604557945e-42, \"text\": \"Bobigny\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bobigny\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bobigny\"}, {\"begin\": 1959, \"end\": 1964, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Denis_of_Paris\", \"score\": 0.9896252684643206, \"rank\": 0.006206427465462191, \"text\": \"Denis\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q43115\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Denis_of_Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Denis_of_Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1990, \"end\": 1995, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.0239926544066172e-28, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Our first stop\", \"from\": 1923, \"to\": 1937}, {\"ngram\": \"an area\", \"from\": 1966, \"to\": 1973}, {\"ngram\": \"the north\", \"from\": 1977, \"to\": 1986}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic\", \"from\": 2001, \"to\": 2008}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 2051, \"to\": 2060}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When we pushed through the brush and into the forest, we found numerous migrant encampments, but none of the promised benefits.\", \"from\": 2062, \"to\": 2189, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the brush\", \"from\": 2085, \"to\": 2094}, {\"ngram\": \"the forest\", \"from\": 2104, \"to\": 2114}, {\"ngram\": \"numerous migrant encampments\", \"from\": 2125, \"to\": 2153}, {\"ngram\": \"none\", \"from\": 2159, \"to\": 2163}, {\"ngram\": \"the promised benefits\", \"from\": 2167, \"to\": 2188}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The outreach workers told us that the Olympics were actually making their job more difficult-the people they assist have been pushed deeper into the shadows, making even finding them a challenge.\", \"from\": 2190, \"to\": 2385, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The outreach workers\", \"from\": 2190, \"to\": 2210}, {\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 2216, \"to\": 2218}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 2224, \"to\": 2236}, {\"ngram\": \"their job\", \"from\": 2258, \"to\": 2267}, {\"ngram\": \"the shadows\", \"from\": 2335, \"to\": 2346}, {\"ngram\": \"a challenge\", \"from\": 2373, \"to\": 2384}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In fact, in our first three stops, we did not come across a single person wanting a doctor's consultation.\", \"from\": 2386, \"to\": 2492, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"fact\", \"from\": 2389, \"to\": 2393}, {\"ngram\": \"our first three stops\", \"from\": 2398, \"to\": 2419}, {\"ngram\": \"a single person\", \"from\": 2444, \"to\": 2459}, {\"ngram\": \"a doctor's consultation\", \"from\": 2468, \"to\": 2491}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This, said Alauzy, was the first time this had happened in six years of doing outreach four nights a week.\", \"from\": 2493, \"to\": 2599, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Alauzy\", \"from\": 2504, \"to\": 2510}, {\"ngram\": \"the first time\", \"from\": 2516, \"to\": 2530}, {\"ngram\": \"six years\", \"from\": 2552, \"to\": 2561}, {\"ngram\": \"outreach\", \"from\": 2571, \"to\": 2579}, {\"ngram\": \"four nights\", \"from\": 2580, \"to\": 2591}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Sometimes the absence of evidence is the evidence itself.\", \"from\": 2600, \"to\": 2657, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the absence\", \"from\": 2610, \"to\": 2621}, {\"ngram\": \"evidence\", \"from\": 2625, \"to\": 2633}, {\"ngram\": \"the evidence\", \"from\": 2637, \"to\": 2649}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But then, as darkness settled over the City of Light, we came upon Abdishakur, a 17-year-old migrant from the Ivory Coast who was setting up his tent in a covered area near the Pompidou Center.\", \"from\": 2659, \"to\": 2852, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2769, \"end\": 2780, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ivory_Coast\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.455783202118749e-21, \"text\": \"Ivory Coast\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ivory_Coast\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ivory_Coast\"}, {\"begin\": 2836, \"end\": 2851, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Centre_Pompidou\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Pompidou Center\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Centre_Pompidou\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Centre_Pompidou\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"darkness\", \"from\": 2672, \"to\": 2680}, {\"ngram\": \"the City\", \"from\": 2694, \"to\": 2702}, {\"ngram\": \"Light\", \"from\": 2706, \"to\": 2711}, {\"ngram\": \"Abdishakur\", \"from\": 2726, \"to\": 2736}, {\"ngram\": \"a 17-year-old migrant\", \"from\": 2738, \"to\": 2759}, {\"ngram\": \"his tent\", \"from\": 2800, \"to\": 2808}, {\"ngram\": \"a covered area\", \"from\": 2812, \"to\": 2826}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He told us that the Olympics had made it much more difficult for him to secure food.\", \"from\": 2853, \"to\": 2937, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 2861, \"to\": 2863}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 2869, \"to\": 2881}, {\"ngram\": \"food\", \"from\": 2932, \"to\": 2936}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He described how, during the Games, police wake him up every day at 5am, screaming at him and his fellow migrants to scatter out of view.\", \"from\": 2938, \"to\": 3075, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 2963, \"to\": 2972}, {\"ngram\": \"police\", \"from\": 2974, \"to\": 2980}, {\"ngram\": \"his fellow migrants\", \"from\": 3032, \"to\": 3051}, {\"ngram\": \"view\", \"from\": 3070, \"to\": 3074}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Many shuffle around the corner and into an underpass where tents sit wedged between a fence and a busy road.\", \"from\": 3076, \"to\": 3184, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Many shuffle\", \"from\": 3076, \"to\": 3088}, {\"ngram\": \"the corner\", \"from\": 3096, \"to\": 3106}, {\"ngram\": \"an underpass\", \"from\": 3116, \"to\": 3128}, {\"ngram\": \"tents\", \"from\": 3135, \"to\": 3140}, {\"ngram\": \"a fence\", \"from\": 3160, \"to\": 3167}, {\"ngram\": \"a busy road\", \"from\": 3172, \"to\": 3183}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Cars whooshed by at high speeds.\", \"from\": 3185, \"to\": 3217, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Cars\", \"from\": 3185, \"to\": 3189}, {\"ngram\": \"high speeds\", \"from\": 3205, \"to\": 3216}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Several of them told us that, for them, the Paris Olympics are more a bane than a boon.\", \"from\": 3218, \"to\": 3305, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 3239, \"to\": 3241}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris Olympics\", \"from\": 3258, \"to\": 3276}, {\"ngram\": \"more a bane\", \"from\": 3281, \"to\": 3292}, {\"ngram\": \"a boon\", \"from\": 3298, \"to\": 3304}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When Abdishakur realized we had a doctor among us, he pulled out a crinkled X-ray of his shoulder and a crumpled manila envelope containing medical papers that he had kept carefully wrapped in plastic, a layer of fabric, and then another layer of plastic to protect them from the elements.\", \"from\": 3307, \"to\": 3596, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3420, \"end\": 3435, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manila_folder\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"manila envelope\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manila_folder\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manila_folder\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Abdishakur\", \"from\": 3312, \"to\": 3322}, {\"ngram\": \"a doctor\", \"from\": 3339, \"to\": 3347}, {\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 3354, \"to\": 3356}, {\"ngram\": \"a crinkled X\", \"from\": 3372, \"to\": 3384}, {\"ngram\": \"ray\", \"from\": 3385, \"to\": 3388}, {\"ngram\": \"his shoulder\", \"from\": 3392, \"to\": 3404}, {\"ngram\": \"medical papers\", \"from\": 3447, \"to\": 3461}, {\"ngram\": \"plastic\", \"from\": 3500, \"to\": 3507}, {\"ngram\": \"a layer\", \"from\": 3509, \"to\": 3516}, {\"ngram\": \"fabric\", \"from\": 3520, \"to\": 3526}, {\"ngram\": \"then another layer\", \"from\": 3532, \"to\": 3550}, {\"ngram\": \"plastic\", \"from\": 3554, \"to\": 3561}, {\"ngram\": \"the elements\", \"from\": 3583, \"to\": 3595}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Dr. Bertrand Chatelain listened patiently as he held the X-ray against a street light, eventually giving him some medication and a referral to a local clinic.\", \"from\": 3597, \"to\": 3755, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Dr. Bertrand Chatelain\", \"from\": 3597, \"to\": 3619}, {\"ngram\": \"the X\", \"from\": 3650, \"to\": 3655}, {\"ngram\": \"ray\", \"from\": 3656, \"to\": 3659}, {\"ngram\": \"a street light\", \"from\": 3668, \"to\": 3682}, {\"ngram\": \"some medication\", \"from\": 3706, \"to\": 3721}, {\"ngram\": \"a referral\", \"from\": 3726, \"to\": 3736}, {\"ngram\": \"a local clinic\", \"from\": 3740, \"to\": 3754}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Meanwhile, dozens of migrants encircled us, lining up for medical assistance.\", \"from\": 3757, \"to\": 3834, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"dozens\", \"from\": 3768, \"to\": 3774}, {\"ngram\": \"migrants\", \"from\": 3778, \"to\": 3786}, {\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 3797, \"to\": 3799}, {\"ngram\": \"medical assistance\", \"from\": 3815, \"to\": 3833}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For the next two and a half hours, Chatelain treated person after person, all of them unaccompanied minors from Africa, mostly the Ivory Coast and Guinea.\", \"from\": 3835, \"to\": 3989, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3966, \"end\": 3977, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ivory_Coast\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.455783202118749e-21, \"text\": \"Ivory Coast\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ivory_Coast\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ivory_Coast\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the next two and a half hours\", \"from\": 3839, \"to\": 3868}, {\"ngram\": \"Chatelain\", \"from\": 3870, \"to\": 3879}, {\"ngram\": \"person\", \"from\": 3888, \"to\": 3894}, {\"ngram\": \"person\", \"from\": 3901, \"to\": 3907}, {\"ngram\": \"Africa\", \"from\": 3947, \"to\": 3953}, {\"ngram\": \"Guinea\", \"from\": 3982, \"to\": 3988}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Abakar Moussa, an Arabic translator who has worked with M\\u00e9decins du Monde since 2018 because, as he told us, he \\\"feels close to the values\\\" of the group, stood by taking notes and plucking the correct medications from the three large bags of supplies that we toted around.\", \"from\": 3990, \"to\": 4262, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4008, \"end\": 4014, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arab_world\", \"score\": 0.999999720969793, \"rank\": 2.7902386550435344e-07, \"text\": \"Arabic\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arab_world\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arab_world\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Abakar Moussa\", \"from\": 3990, \"to\": 4003}, {\"ngram\": \"M\\u00e9decins du Monde\", \"from\": 4046, \"to\": 4063}, {\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 4095, \"to\": 4097}, {\"ngram\": \"the values\", \"from\": 4118, \"to\": 4128}, {\"ngram\": \"the group\", \"from\": 4133, \"to\": 4142}, {\"ngram\": \"notes\", \"from\": 4160, \"to\": 4165}, {\"ngram\": \"the correct medications\", \"from\": 4179, \"to\": 4202}, {\"ngram\": \"the three large bags\", \"from\": 4208, \"to\": 4228}, {\"ngram\": \"supplies\", \"from\": 4232, \"to\": 4240}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Alauzy darted about, engaging in friendly banter with the young migrants and assisting Moussa as needed.\", \"from\": 4263, \"to\": 4367, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Alauzy\", \"from\": 4263, \"to\": 4269}, {\"ngram\": \"friendly banter\", \"from\": 4296, \"to\": 4311}, {\"ngram\": \"the young migrants\", \"from\": 4317, \"to\": 4335}, {\"ngram\": \"Moussa\", \"from\": 4350, \"to\": 4356}]}, {\"sentence\": \"TheOlympic Charterextols \\\"the educational value of good example, social responsibility and respect for internationally recognised human rights and universal fundamental ethical principles.\\\"\", \"from\": 4369, \"to\": 4558, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"TheOlympic Charterextols\", \"from\": 4369, \"to\": 4393}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"the educational value\", \"from\": 4394, \"to\": 4416}, {\"ngram\": \"good example\", \"from\": 4420, \"to\": 4432}, {\"ngram\": \"social responsibility\", \"from\": 4434, \"to\": 4455}, {\"ngram\": \"respect\", \"from\": 4460, \"to\": 4467}, {\"ngram\": \"internationally recognised human rights\", \"from\": 4472, \"to\": 4511}, {\"ngram\": \"universal fundamental ethical principles\", \"from\": 4516, \"to\": 4556}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This team from M\\u00e9decins du Monde was quietly putting those values into action, far from the hot glare of the Olympic media hype machine.\", \"from\": 4559, \"to\": 4695, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"This team\", \"from\": 4559, \"to\": 4568}, {\"ngram\": \"M\\u00e9decins\"