", \"from\": 9002, \"to\": 9016}, {\"ngram\": \"the social component\", \"from\": 9049, \"to\": 9069}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 9073, \"to\": 9082}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Chellian lamented this \\\"missed opportunity,\\\" adding that \\\"the people in the streets\\\" have been left behind.\", \"from\": 9135, \"to\": 9242, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9135, \"end\": 9143, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chellian\", \"score\": 0.9999999994242899, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Chellian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chellian\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chellian\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"this \\\"missed opportunity\", \"from\": 9153, \"to\": 9177}, {\"ngram\": \"the people\", \"from\": 9193, \"to\": 9203}, {\"ngram\": \"the streets\", \"from\": 9207, \"to\": 9218}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The hypergentrified city keeps the most marginalized out of its territory,\\\" France-based writer Cole Stangler notes inhis bookParis Is Not Dead: Surviving Hypergentrification in the City of Light.\", \"from\": 9244, \"to\": 9441, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9341, \"end\": 9345, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cole_Turner\", \"score\": 0.9999972946962075, \"rank\": 2.7053098050388666e-06, \"text\": \"Cole\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cole_Turner\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cole_Turner\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The hypergentrified city\", \"from\": 9245, \"to\": 9269}, {\"ngram\": \"its territory\", \"from\": 9305, \"to\": 9318}, {\"ngram\": \"inhis\", \"from\": 9361, \"to\": 9366}, {\"ngram\": \"bookParis\", \"from\": 9367, \"to\": 9376}, {\"ngram\": \"Hypergentrification\", \"from\": 9400, \"to\": 9419}, {\"ngram\": \"the City\", \"from\": 9423, \"to\": 9431}, {\"ngram\": \"Light\", \"from\": 9435, \"to\": 9440}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This dynamic has been turbocharged in Olympic Paris.\", \"from\": 9442, \"to\": 9494, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9488, \"end\": 9493, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.0239926544066172e-28, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"This dynamic\", \"from\": 9442, \"to\": 9454}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It breaks up families.\", \"from\": 9495, \"to\": 9517, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"families\", \"from\": 9508, \"to\": 9516}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It uproots people's lives.\", \"from\": 9518, \"to\": 9544, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"people's lives\", \"from\": 9529, \"to\": 9543}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And it is cruel.\", \"from\": 9545, \"to\": 9561, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"One reporter was overheard saying that there were not any compelling off-the-field stories at this year's Olympics.\", \"from\": 9562, \"to\": 9677, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"One reporter\", \"from\": 9562, \"to\": 9574}, {\"ngram\": \"the-field\", \"from\": 9635, \"to\": 9644}, {\"ngram\": \"this year's Olympics\", \"from\": 9656, \"to\": 9676}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Peter KornbluhandWilliam M. LeoGrande Column/Sasha Abramsky David Faris Amber Husain Actually, there are 12,500.\", \"from\": 9679, \"to\": 9795, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Peter KornbluhandWilliam M. LeoGrande Column/Sasha Abramsky\", \"from\": 9679, \"to\": 9738}, {\"ngram\": \"David Faris Amber Husain\", \"from\": 9739, \"to\": 9763}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But you have to want to look.\", \"from\": 9796, \"to\": 9825, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Around midnight, as we packed our bags and prepared to walk back to the M\\u00e9decins du Monde van, Abdishakur had wedged himself between two tents where, amid the hustle and sirens of Olympic Paris, he performed his Islamic prayers.\", \"from\": 9827, \"to\": 10055, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 10015, \"end\": 10020, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.0239926544066172e-28, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"midnight\", \"from\": 9834, \"to\": 9842}, {\"ngram\": \"our bags\", \"from\": 9857, \"to\": 9865}, {\"ngram\": \"the M\\u00e9decins du Monde van\", \"from\": 9895, \"to\": 9920}, {\"ngram\": \"Abdishakur\", \"from\": 9922, \"to\": 9932}, {\"ngram\": \"two tents\", \"from\": 9960, \"to\": 9969}, {\"ngram\": \"the hustle\", \"from\": 9982, \"to\": 9992}, {\"ngram\": \"sirens\", \"from\": 9997, \"to\": 10003}, {\"ngram\": \"his Islamic prayers\", \"from\": 10035, \"to\": 10054}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Behind him was a wall bearing the ubiquitous purple signage for the Paris 2024 Olympics.\", \"from\": 10056, \"to\": 10144, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 10130, \"end\": 10143, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"2024 Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a wall\", \"from\": 10071, \"to\": 10077}, {\"ngram\": \"the ubiquitous purple signage\", \"from\": 10086, \"to\": 10115}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The wall might as well have been surrounded by barbed wire.\", \"from\": 10145, \"to\": 10204, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The wall\", \"from\": 10145, \"to\": 10153}, {\"ngram\": \"barbed wire\", \"from\": 10192, \"to\": 10203}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris will almost certainly be remembered as a successful Olympic site.\", \"from\": 10206, \"to\": 10277, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 10206, \"end\": 10211, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.0239926544066172e-28, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a successful Olympic site\", \"from\": 10251, \"to\": 10276}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Such recollections, however, will leave out those who suffered under its weight.\", \"from\": 10278, \"to\": 10358, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Such recollections\", \"from\": 10278, \"to\": 10296}, {\"ngram\": \"its weight\", \"from\": 10347, \"to\": 10357}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They will ignore that one measure of \\\"success\\\" for politicians and Olympic organizers will have required the cruel disappearance of people like Abdishakur.\", \"from\": 10359, \"to\": 10514, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"that one measure\", \"from\": 10376, \"to\": 10392}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"success\", \"from\": 10396, \"to\": 10404}, {\"ngram\": \"politicians\", \"from\": 10410, \"to\": 10421}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic organizers\", \"from\": 10426, \"to\": 10444}, {\"ngram\": \"the cruel disappearance\", \"from\": 10464, \"to\": 10487}, {\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 10491, \"to\": 10497}, {\"ngram\": \"Abdishakur\", \"from\": 10503, \"to\": 10513}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As Los Angeles readies for the 2028 Olympics, California's unhoused people are already being subjected toan appalling agenda of displacement.\", \"from\": 10516, \"to\": 10657, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 10562, \"end\": 10572, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.1870261011799685e-23, \"text\": \"California\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the 2028 Olympics\", \"from\": 10543, \"to\": 10560}, {\"ngram\": \"toan appalling agenda\", \"from\": 10619, \"to\": 10640}, {\"ngram\": \"displacement\", \"from\": 10644, \"to\": 10656}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We need to shine light on the social crimes of Olympic Paris now, or they will be replicated on our own shores.\", \"from\": 10658, \"to\": 10769, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 10713, \"end\": 10718, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.0239926544066172e-28, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"light\", \"from\": 10675, \"to\": 10680}, {\"ngram\": \"the social crimes\", \"from\": 10684, \"to\": 10701}, {\"ngram\": \"our own shores\", \"from\": 10754, \"to\": 10768}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Even before February 28, the reasons for Donald Trump's imploding approval rating were abundantly clear: untrammeled corruption and personal enrichment to the tune of billions of dollars during an affordability crisis, a foreign policy guided only by his own derelict sense of morality, and the deployment of a murderous campaign of occupation, detention, and deportation on American streets.\", \"from\": 10771, \"to\": 11163, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 10812, \"end\": 10824, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\", \"score\": 0.9999998371850002, \"rank\": 1.6281542326113093e-07, \"text\": \"Donald Trump\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\"}, {\"begin\": 11146, \"end\": 11154, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.038915027724694e-21, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"February\", \"from\": 10783, \"to\": 10791}, {\"ngram\": \"the reasons\", \"from\": 10796, \"to\": 10807}, {\"ngram\": \"untrammeled corruption\